CREATING A NEW USER  -  March 1993  -  David W Jeske

Quick and Dirty

check /sm for a un-used user number.

Remember, /sm is regularly updated every morning at 6am. If you wish to
manually update it. Type /MEMUD and wait for the messages which will appear
on the "System Channel" (T0). See /sysmon.

when you find a free user number.

type /u<number>

Enter the User Edit Password

If that user number exists it will automatically put you in to a user
editor. If that user number is empty, it will automatically put you into
the NEW user section.

ALTERNATIVELY:  You can type /u<return>, enter the user edit password,
                And select (N)ew User from the menu.


